The image rectification is to make the epipolar  lines of two camera images horizontally aligned. This may be accomplished by using linear transformations that rotate, translate and skew the camera images.\newline
The principle of image rectification is shown in  figure 2.5. The original camera image planes are drawn with solid borders and the rectified image planes are drawn with dashed borders. Epipolar lines are also drawn from the projected points p and p'to epipoles e and e'\newline
